This is not the best practice, as your books are stored on your server&#39;s **RAM**. So, reconsider to setup a database to assist the data relations. And in fact, spring provide jpa&#39;s [`@Entity`](https://www.baeldung.com/jpa-entities) to assist you for this kind of thing. When you declared your book as an entity, such as

```
@Entity
